such a radical surgery.

92
00:04:29,403 --> 00:04:32,037
- More tests?
- Yes.

93
00:04:32,139 --> 00:04:36,024
Dr. Yang, you'll be
assisting Dr. Shepherd today.

94
00:04:36,126 --> 00:04:39,961
Personal relationships,
personal loyalties

95
00:04:40,064 --> 00:04:42,747
and personal favorites
will no longer be a factor

96
00:04:42,849 --> 00:04:44,266
in our training program.

97
00:04:44,368 --> 00:04:48,486
Attendings, you will spread
your wealth of knowledge equally

98
00:04:48,588 --> 00:04:50,305
among all of the residents.

99
00:04:50,407 --> 00:04:52,357
In addition, we'll
refocus our attention

100
00:04:52,459 --> 00:04:56,328
on patient communication and
bedside manner. For some of us,

101
00:04:56,430 --> 00:05:00,932
this means learning the lost
art of humanity and compassion.

102
00:05:01,034 --> 00:05:04,269
For others, this means
learning how to treat patients

103
00:05:04,371 --> 00:05:07,905
without becoming
emotionally involved with them.

104
00:05:08,008 --> 00:05:11,325
Shelley Boden, 30, stage four
colon cancer with liver mets.

105
00:05:11,428 --> 00:05:14,295
Shelley has been through
extensive chemo and radiation.

106
00:05:14,397 --> 00:05:18,182
According to the CT, a liver
resection could be curative.

107
00:05:18,284 --> 00:05:20,251
Will be curative. Will.

108
00:05:20,336 --> 00:05:22,754
Do you have any
other questions for us?

109
00:05:22,856 --> 00:05:25,757
What happens if you find
more cancer than you expect?

110
00:05:25,859 --> 00:05:28,210
No, Jen. A, that's
not gonna happen.

111
00:05:28,312 --> 00:05:32,413
B, Izzie's already answered
all of your questions three times.

112
00:05:32,515 --> 00:05:36,768
- Izzie's not the main surgeon.
- Izzie's awesome. We love Izzie.

113
00:05:36,853 --> 00:05:39,237
This is Dr. Grey. She'll
prep you for surgery

114
00:05:39,339 --> 00:05:41,417
and answer any
questions you have.

115
00:05:41,441 --> 00:05:44,810
- Izzie's not staying?
- This is a surgical program.

116
00:05:44,912 --> 00:05:47,306
Psychiatry is
on the fifth floor.

117
00:05:47,330 --> 00:05:49,230
Let's not confuse the two.

118
00:05:50,234 --> 00:05:52,333
In addition, residents,

119
00:05:52,435 --> 00:05:55,971
your interns reflect on you.

120
00:05:56,073 --> 00:05:58,039
If they fail, you fail.

121
00:05:58,141 --> 00:06:00,558
If they succeed, you succeed.

122
00:06:00,660 --> 00:06:04,378
Attendings, that goes
for residents as well.

123
00:06:05,148 --> 00:06:07,165
Teach with enthusiasm.

124
00:06:07,267 --> 00:06:10,334
Learn with enthusiasm.

125
