Right.

241
00:13:28,625 --> 00:13:31,426
How's he doing? Think
we're looking at a lawsuit?

242
00:13:31,528 --> 00:13:34,345
No, we don't have a
picture yet, but... no.

243
00:13:34,447 --> 00:13:36,887
This guy doesn't seem
like the lawsuit type.

244
00:13:36,966 --> 00:13:38,983
Let's hope you're right.

245
00:13:53,883 --> 00:13:55,649
Hello?

246
00:13:59,422 --> 00:14:00,938
Hello?

247
00:14:02,408 --> 00:14:05,343
I cannot apologize enough.

248
00:14:05,445 --> 00:14:07,965
Treat him like a king.
Hear that, Mr. O'Brien?

249
00:14:08,014 --> 00:14:10,314
Dr. Karev is going to
take great care of you.

250
00:14:10,416 --> 00:14:13,234
You are our number
one priority today.

251
00:14:13,336 --> 00:14:14,947
- Are you OK?
- God hates me.

252
00:14:14,971 --> 00:14:17,989
- Mr. O'Brien...
- My wife left me.

253
00:14:18,091 --> 00:14:20,358
My accountant stole from me.

254
00:14:21,261 --> 00:14:24,562
The store I worked
at burned down.

255
00:14:24,664 --> 00:14:28,433
I was diagnosed with an aneurysm
for which I'd require surgery

256
00:14:28,535 --> 00:14:32,269
in a hospital that seems
to be crumbling around me.

257
00:14:33,222 --> 00:14:34,955
God hates me.

258
00:14:36,475 --> 00:14:39,544
You can see the remaining
tumors easily identified here.

259
00:14:39,645 --> 00:14:41,712
Her liver looks so healthy.

260
00:14:41,814 --> 00:14:44,294
That's the beauty
of general surgery.

261
00:14:44,367 --> 00:14:46,651
See badness
surrounded by goodness.

262
00:14:46,753 --> 00:14:49,770
Cut out the badness,
all's right with the world.

263
00:14:49,873 --> 00:14:52,856
It's just you and your scalpel,

264
00:14:52,959 --> 00:14:56,710
one on one,<i> mano a mano.</i>

265
00:14:59,232 --> 00:15:01,933
OK, this is me teaching
with enthusiasm.

266
00:15:05,855 --> 00:15:08,072
Oh...

267
00:15:08,174 --> 00:15:10,341
Oh, no.

268
00:15:16,048 --> 00:15:18,065
- O'Malley.
- What?!

269
00:15:21,904 --> 00:15:26,273
Um... if you're
finished with your test...

270
00:15:26,376 --> 00:15:29,377
Look, the hospital's
flooding. The CT's on the fritz,

271
00:15:29,479 --> 00:15:32,347
my post-op and pre-op
patients are backed up for days,

272
00:15:32,449 --> 00:15:34,426
I gotta get a
handle on this thing

273
00:15:34,450 --> 00:15:37,818
before the patients find out and
our ranking drops way past 12.

274
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:41,689
I found a nice, quiet room in
Psych for you to take your exam.

275
00:15:42,692 --> 00:15:45,093
Oh, I see. Um...

276
00:15:45,195 --> 00:15:47,095
No, you go ahead.

277
00:15:52,935 --> 00:15:54,986
Chief!

278
00:15:55,088 --> 00:15:57,939
I am your intern at
least for one more day.

279
00:15:58,041 --> 00:15:59,506
I can help.

280
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:06,747
- Dr. Shepherd, a word.
- Excuse me. Yes?

281
00:16:06,849 --> 00:16:09,417
You mind if I run a
quick test on your patient?

282
00:16:09,519 --> 00:16:12,569
He's in a lot of pain. I don't
think he needs a tummy tuck.

283
00:16:12,671 --> 00:16:15,956
That's funny. No, Dr. Grey came
to me with an interesting idea.

284
00:16:16,058 --> 00:16:19,777
Unlike you, I'm taking the Chief's
new teaching protocol seriously

285
00:16:19,879 --> 00:16:21,128
so I listened.

286
00:16:21,230 --> 00:16:22,964
I read a thing about swelling

287
00:16:23,066 --> 00:16:24,865
and compression
of the ethmoid nerve.

288
00:16:24,967 --> 00:16:28,219
I believe if we were to stick
a cottle elevator up his nose...

289
00:16:28,321 --> 00:16:29,620
I'm sorry, up his nose?

290
00:16:29,722 --> 00:16:31,905
If Dr. Grey is on
the right track,

291
00:16:32,007 --> 00:16:33,608
the patient'll let us know.

292
00:16:34,977 --> 00:16:36,477
OK.

293
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:39,013
Mr. Patmore, I'm Dr. Sloan,

294
00:16:39,115 --> 00:16:42,099
head of plastic surgery and an
ear, nose and throat specialist.

295
00:16:42,184 --> 00:16:44,351
I'd like to run a test
with your permission.

296
00:16:44,454 --> 00:16:46,954
I've seen 16 ENT's.
Not one could help me.

297
00:16:48,374 --> 00:16:50,408
Now breathe normally.

298
00:16:51,210 --> 00:16:53,511
I'm gonna angle this into here.

299
00:16:55,748 --> 00:16:59,050
Let me know when you
feel any... pain or anything.

300
00:16:59,152 --> 00:17:03,370
That's it. That's the pain!

301
00:17:03,472 --> 00:17:05,923
That's what's causing the pain.

302
00:17:06,025 --> 00:17:09,060
Oh, my God! Oh, my God.

303
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:16,517
Anterior ethmoid
neurovascular complex.

304
00:17:16,619 --> 00:17:19,920
A simple middle
turbinectomy will fix it.

305
00:17:20,022 --> 00:17:23,024
Unless you still want to
chop out the front of his brain.

306
00:17:25,278 --> 00:17:26,877
Nicely done.

307
00:17:34,604 --> 00:17:36,003
Hi.

308
00:17:39,776 --> 00:17:41,325
How'd it go?

309
00:17:41,427 --> 00:17:42,993
Hi, Shelley.

310
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:49,583
We found that the mets were much
more extensive than the CT detected,

311
00:17:49,685 --> 00:17:54,171
and the main tumor actually
extended in and around

312
00:17:54,273 --> 00:17:56,957
the major blood
vessel behind the liver.

313
00:17:57,059 --> 00:17:59,894
We're gonna start a new
round of chemo, that's all.

314
00:17:59,996 --> 00:18:01,807
I already have a call
in to your oncologist.

315
00:18:01,831 --> 00:18:07,301
That's him. I'll be right back.

316
00:18:11,274 --> 00:18:12,839
We can manage your pain.

317
00:18:12,941 --> 00:18:15,976
I'm sorry we don't
have better news.

318
00:18:32,428 --> 00:18:36,663
So did you decide what to
do about your roommates?

319
00:18:41,037 --> 00:18:43,070
I'm so sorry, Shelley.

320
00:18:44,157 --> 00:18:46,273
Come on.

321
00:18:48,461 --> 00:18:51,562
So how good is the
hot boyfriend in bed?

322
00:19:03,459 --> 00:19:06,928
Look, we don't even
know what we are yet.

323
00:19:07,030 --> 00:19:11,432
So how does Mark Sloan know?

324
00:19:11,534 --> 00:19:15,368
Why are you talking
to him instead of me?

325
00:19:16,989 --> 00:19:18,439
Ladies.

326
00:19:21,660 --> 00:19:23,027
Am I interrupting?

327
00:19:23,129 --> 00:19:25,729
- Your timing is perfect.
- Really?

328
00:19:25,831 --> 00:19:28,249
Were you about to feel her up?

329
00:19:31,637 --> 00:19:33,670
- Stop. You have to stop.
- I can't.

330
00:19:33,772 --> 00:19:36,089
- Seriously, she hates it.
- That's why I can't.

331
00:19:36,191 --> 00:19:39,594
- Don't... You want a spanking? I...
- OK?

332
00:19:42,899 --> 00:19:45,466
You told Derek you think
I should kick them out?

333
00:19:45,568 --> 00:19:48,752
No. No, I...

334
00:19:48,854 --> 00:19:51,099
I told him I would want
them out. Me, not you.

335
00:19:51,123 --> 00:19:53,808
I only said it because
he wouldn't stop talking.

336
00:19:53,910 --> 00:19:57,645
You don't think I should? I think
I'm going to. It's the adult thing to do.

337
00:19:57,747 --> 00:20:00,547
- What does your shrink say?
- I quit my shrink.

338
00:20:01,768 --> 00:20:04,869
- I'm happy. We're happy.
- Can I sit here?

339
00:20:06,138 --> 00:20:08,973
George... George, how did it go?

340
00:20:11,593 --> 00:20:15,346
There's a water problem.
I'm just trying to help the Chief.

341
00:20:15,448 --> 00:20:18,015
Now the medical facts
are falling out of my ear.

342
00:20:18,117 --> 00:20:19,967
Eat this, it's brain food.

343
00:20:21,270 --> 00:20:22,837
My dude with the aneurysm?

344
00:20:22,939 --> 00:20:25,690
Fell in the water, smacked
his head, got stuck in the CT.

345
00:20:25,791 --> 00:20:28,904
My patient's dying. I hate it
when I like them and they're dying.

346
00:20:28,928 --> 00:20:31,679
Our guy's been in pain at
a eight the last seven years

347
00:20:31,781 --> 00:20:34,698
because of an inflamed
nerve in his nose.

348
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:36,717
I wish I had an inflamed nerve.

349
00:20:36,819 --> 00:20:40,070
There is no way that guy's been
living at an eight. He's a wimp.

350
00:20:40,172 --> 00:20:42,289
His eight? My
three. I can take pain.

351
00:20:42,391 --> 00:20:44,475
You can't talk to my
boyfriend for ten minutes.

352
00:20:44,577 --> 00:20:48,479
There's pain and then there's
torture. I can take pain. Test me.

353
00:20:50,849 --> 00:20:52,516
- Nothing.
- Impressive.

354
00:20:52,601 --> 00:20:55,920
Shut up! You barely touched her.

355
00:20:57,073 --> 00:20:59,606
- Ow!
- Ow! No! No!

356
00:20:59,708 --> 00:21:02,710
- Knock it off! Stop it!
- How did you diagnose
that nerve?

357
00:21:02,812 --> 00:21:05,345
Because I've never
heard of that condition.

358
00:21:05,447 --> 00:21:08,348
I remembered an article
from the British journal of ENT.

359
00:21:08,450 --> 00:21:13,938
It was issue 47,
page 19, from 1964.

360
00:21:14,040 --> 00:21:16,740
- A photographic memory.
- Dude. Lexipedia.

361
00:21:16,842 --> 00:21:19,793
- Oh, I hate you.
- Don't hate me. I can help you.

362
00:21:23,982 --> 00:21:25,950
Chief, what's going
on with the flood?

363
00:21:26,052 --> 00:21:29,186
It's not a flood,
Bailey. It's a pipe that...

364
00:21:29,288 --> 00:21:31,768
It's minor, OK? Not to worry.

365
00:21:31,824 --> 00:21:33,936
Aren't you headed to surgery?

366
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:35,526
Yes, sir.

367
00:21:36,812 --> 00:21:38,879
Chief, a few months ago

368
00:21:38,981 --> 00:21:42,282
little Tuck flushed one of his
action figures down the toilet.

369
00:21:42,384 --> 00:21:44,446
I thought it was
no big deal. Minor.

370
00:21:44,470 --> 00:21:46,987
But then I came
home to a kitchen

371
00:21:47,089 --> 00:21:49,840
filled with several
inches of poop water.

372
00:21:51,093 --> 00:21:54,061
- Poop water?
- In my kitchen, sir.

373
00:21:56,232 --> 00:21:59,466
Thank you, Dr. Bailey,
but I have this under control.

374
00:22:00,136 --> 00:22:01,568
Yes, sir.

375
00:22:03,956 --> 00:22:05,589
Poop water.

376
00:22:05,691 --> 00:22:09,610
Hey. Hey. So apparently
there's some kind of leak.

377
00:22:09,712 --> 00:22:12,512
Chief wants me to move the
pre-op patients to the clinic.

378
00:22:12,615 --> 00:22:14,231
Who's free to help me...? Ow!

379
00:22:14,333 --> 00:22:16,867
- What the hell?
- Not a high pain threshold?

380
00:22:16,952 --> 00:22:19,670
You know what? Throw
him out. Not me, just him.

381
00:22:19,772 --> 00:22:22,434
- She likes me more.
- I bake for everyone
and I clean.

382
00:22:22,458 --> 00:22:24,302
The only thing you
bring to the house is filth.

383
00:22:24,326 --> 00:22:28,646
What would you prefer,
chocolate cake or an STD?

384
00:22:29,732 --> 00:22:31,799
Water!

385
00:22:31,901 --> 00:22:34,368
- Get out, get out.
- Where is this coming from?

386
00:22:34,470 --> 00:22:37,637
- Get the Chief.
- Let's keep going.

387
00:22:40,059 --> 00:22:42,475
Post-ops to rooms 2415.

388
00:22:42,577 --> 00:22:45,412
Pre-ops to rooms 2233, 4 and 5.

389
00:22:45,514 --> 00:22:47,747
- Overflow goes into the clinic.
- OK.

390
00:22:47,850 --> 00:22:49,150
Chief!

391
00:22:49,252 --> 00:22:51,352
I got everything
under control up here.

392
00:22:51,454 --> 00:22:54,488
I need you to oversee Stevens
with the pre-ops in the clinic.

393
00:22:54,590 --> 00:22:57,875
Sir, maybe we need to shut down.

394
00:22:57,977 --> 00:23:00,594
Just send the patients to
Mercy West, Seattle Pres.

395
00:23:00,696 --> 00:23:03,881
They can repair the pipe. We'll
be up and running in no time.

396
00:23:03,983 --> 00:23:06,250
I am sending our
patients to dry ground.

397
00:23:06,352 --> 00:23:07,901
I closed all but two ORs.

398
00:23:08,004 --> 00:23:11,672
Maintenance has isolated the
broken pipe, so thank you, Dr. Bailey.

399
00:23:11,774 --> 00:23:15,042
When I say I've got it under
control that's what I mean.

400
00:23:15,144 --> 00:23:18,712
Sir, they may have isolated
it, but a lot of water got out.

401
00:23:18,814 --> 00:23:22,082
- I'm just saying...
- Dr. Bailey, clinic now!

402
00:23:25,687 --> 00:23:28,505
Yes, sir. On my way.

403
00:23:29,508 --> 00:23:31,408
Slow down!

404
00:23:35,565 --> 00:23:37,998
OK, what next?

405
00:23:38,100 --> 00:23:40,117
Wait. Are you sure
you have time for this?

406
00:23:40,219 --> 00:23:42,430
I want you to get
to take your test.

407
00:23:42,454 --> 00:23:44,214
- Thank you.
- Grey.

408
00:23:45,741 --> 00:23:48,826
Despite your
unfortunate taste in men,

409
00:23:48,928 --> 00:23:50,589
turns out you're
not entirely useless.

410
00:23:50,613 --> 00:23:53,780
Mr. Patmore's condition
is extremely rare...

411
00:23:53,883 --> 00:23:56,116
and you nailed it.

412
00:23:56,218 --> 00:23:58,402
You can scrub in.

413
00:23:58,504 --> 00:24:01,271
Now? You're doing the
surgery now, with the flood?

414
00:24:01,373 --> 00:24:04,742
Flood's contained. Our man's
been in pain for seven years.

415
00:24:04,844 --> 00:24:06,444
See you in surgery.

416
00:24:06,546 --> 00:24:09,396
I can't. I'm sorry. Um...

417
00:24:09,498 --> 00:24:14,117
But I'm really busy helping
the Chief... the Chief's intern.

418
00:24:14,219 --> 00:24:16,720
I... Thank you, but
maybe next time?

419
00:24:16,805 --> 00:24:19,673
No, Lassie, there
won't be a next time.

420
00:24:20,909 --> 00:24:23,076
Pathetic.

421
00:24:23,178 --> 00:24:25,279
Mr. Patmore, I'm
gonna draw some blood

422
00:24:25,381 --> 00:24:28,715
and place a topical decongestant
before I take you to surgery.

423
00:24:28,817 --> 00:24:30,284
Absolutely, of course.

424
00:24:31,253 --> 00:24:33,613
How's your pain level now?

425
00:24:34,039 --> 00:24:35,506
Eight.

426
00:24:36,241 --> 00:24:37,841
It's always at eight.

427
00:24:37,943 --> 00:24:40,994
Oh. It looked like
you had some relief.

428
00:24:42,765 --> 00:24:44,765
I've spent seven years.

429
00:24:44,867 --> 00:24:47,317
I've seen 39 doctors.

430
00:24:48,888 --> 00:24:52,106
I've tried every kind of
painkiller and nothing helps.

431
00:24:52,208 --> 00:24:55,109
I've had doctors tell
me it's my imagination...

432
00:24:56,779 --> 00:24:58,628
that I'm crazy.

433
00:24:58,731 --> 00:25:00,797
Called me a drug addict.

434
00:25:07,206 --> 00:25:09,056
My wife died last year.

435
00:25:12,094 --> 00:25:15,261
After spending years carting
me around to doctor after doctor,

436
00:25:15,363 --> 00:25:18,749
test after test, she died.

437
00:25:21,353 --> 00:25:23,620
She was my best friend.

438
00:25:25,457 --> 00:25:27,992
She was my favorite
person in the...

439
00:25:28,761 --> 00:25:30,494
And she died.

440
00:25:32,748 --> 00:25:35,015
But I couldn't feel it.

441
00:25:38,354 --> 00:25:39,837
I couldn't feel that pain

442
00:25:39,939 --> 00:25:43,624
because I was so completely
occupied with this one.

443
00:25:46,195 --> 00:25:49,763
Now I finally know what's
wrong and Dr. Sloan is gonna fix it

444
00:25:49,865 --> 00:25:54,985
so you're right, you're right,
that I'm feeling some relief.

445
00:25:58,691 --> 00:26:01,175
OK, let's get your blood drawn.

446
00:26:04,914 --> 00:26:07,447
I'm not gonna do it. I'm
not gonna have surgery.

447
00:26:07,550 --> 00:26:09,683
It's just gonna hurt.

448
00:26:09,785 --> 00:26:12,402
She's gonna slice me in
half and probably kill me.

449
00:26:12,504 --> 00:26:16,489
If she doesn't kill me,
it'll just hurt like hell.

450
00:26:16,609 --> 00:26:19,593
Probably get infected and
hurt worse. I'm not gonna do it.

451
00:26:19,695 --> 00:26:23,664
I get that you're scared, but if you
want to live you need the surgery.

452
00:26:23,766 --> 00:26:26,800
If I want to live? Have you
been paying any attention?

453
00:26:33,275 --> 00:26:36,243
My girlfriend had a hysterical
pregnancy and went nuts,

454
00:26:36,345 --> 00:26:39,558
cut her wrists while I was in the
next room, had to be committed.

455
00:26:39,582 --> 00:26:41,932
Now my roommate's
planning to make me move.

456
00:26:42,034 --> 00:26:43,411
I have no money for a deposit.

457
00:26:43,435 --> 00:26:45,936
Chances are next
week I'm homeless.

458
00:26:49,107 --> 00:26:51,508
You're making stuff up
to make me feel better?

459
00:26:51,610 --> 00:26:53,844
You must have
something to live for.

460
00:26:55,347 --> 00:26:58,031
Or even just the
possibility of something.

461
00:27:00,486 --> 00:27:02,385
This girl at the grocery store.

462
00:27:04,056 --> 00:27:06,657
I keep meaning to say hello.

463
00:27:06,759 --> 00:27:10,661
Instead I... just keep
asking her about the produce.

464
00:27:10,763 --> 00:27:12,896
All right. So you
get the surgery.

465
00:27:12,981 --> 00:27:16,984
'Cause chances are your
luck's gonna turn around.

466
00:27:17,086 --> 00:27:20,720
It's science. It's
the law of averages.

467
00:27:20,822 --> 00:27:22,689
It's gonna turn around.

468
00:27:22,791 --> 00:27:26,576
And when it does, you say hello.

469
00:27:28,664 --> 00:27:30,347
I say hello.

470
00:27:45,881 --> 00:27:47,347
Chips?

471
00:27:48,483 --> 00:27:49,682
Chocolate?

472
00:27:52,754 --> 00:27:54,087
Thanks.

473
00:28:00,328 --> 00:28:04,364
- What?
- You're not a terrible person.

474
00:28:04,466 --> 00:28:07,518
- OK.
- I know we don't see
eye to eye, but...

475
00:28:09,355 --> 00:28:12,188
I found this really
great apartment.

476
00:28:12,290 --> 00:28:16,025
It's across the street from
the hospital, has great light.

477
00:28:16,127 --> 00:28:18,878
I know you can afford
it and it's Burke-free.

478
00:28:19,949 --> 00:28:22,849
It must be kind of awful
living in his old place.

479
00:28:24,135 --> 00:28:25,652
Think about it.

480
00:28:36,431 --> 00:28:40,484
You can open that retractor up
more if you want to get a better look.

481
00:28:40,586 --> 00:28:43,086
Just make sure you keep
the small bowel inside.

482
00:28:43,188 --> 00:28:45,138
I want to avoid a post-op ileus.

483
00:28:45,240 --> 00:28:49,225
We better. He thinks there's a
